<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,403,535]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Comments: According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser" box="[487,644,439,463]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 303" refId="ref40781" refString="Nieser, N. (1975) The water bugs (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha) of the Guyana Region. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 16, 1 - 303." type="journal article" year="1975">Nieser (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, this is known only from the male 
<typeStatus box="[1029,1077,440,464]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1155,1230,439,463]" name="Brazil" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Brazil</collectingCountry>
”; the records from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,258,476,500]" name="Suriname" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Suriname</collectingCountry>
in fact correspond to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kevan, 1948)" baseAuthorityName="Kevan" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[504,810,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" genus="Cryptovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis box="[504,638,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. terrestris</emphasis>
(Kevan, 1948)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnack and Estevez" box="[821,1139,476,500]" firstAuthor="Schnack" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="346 - 380" refId="ref42963" refString="Schnack, J. A. &amp; Estevez, A. L. (1979) Monografia sistematica de los Gelastocoridae de la Republica Argentina (Hemiptera). Limnobios, 1, 346 - 380." type="journal article" year="1979">Schnack and Estévez (1979)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the species from the South Region (SC).
</paragraph>
